HEADWORD: Glutazine
<hw>Glu"ta*zine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A nitrogenous substance, forming a heavy, sandy powder, white or
nearly so. It is a derivative of pyridine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gluteal</ent>⟦br⟧
